inn1.comm: Malinga slides it down the leg side and Australia open their account, courtesy a wide
bowled on a good length outside off, Warner shapes up for a cut but it's a touch too close to play that shot, misses it
nipped back in sharply after pitching and also swung in, struck Warner high on the pads as it beat him after moving in, they steal a legbye, would have gone over comfortably
Malinga gets that swing in as well, this one is outside off stump and Wade shoulders arms to that one

beaten completely, beaten through the gate, swinging in and Wade played a little outside the line to that one, missed it and it just went over the stumps, there is an appeal for caught behind but that flicked the trousers on the way to the keeper
swing again, lands on a good length outside off, Wade stabs that towards extra cover
thrashed, pitched up, a reasonable amount of width and Wade cashes in, creaming it past extra cover for a boundary
angles that wide of the off stump and it goes away further after pitching, Warner leaves it alone, called a wide by Asad Rauf
swing, some outswing for Kula, lands on a good length on the off, Warner shuffles across a hint and defends it into the leg side
bowled on a good length on middle and off, rocks on the back foot, defended into the off side
slightly short on leg stump, turns it behind square for a single
a touch too straight, short of a good length, worked away past mid-on for a single
too wide and Warner doesn't let it go to waste, reaches for it and crashes it through the covers for a boundary
short of a good length on middle, gets back and across and pushes it back down the pitch
pitched on a length on middle and leg, driven firmly towards mid-on and it goes through Dammika, three more to the score, Dammika slid to his left but couldn't quite stop that
short of a good length on middle, pushed off the back foot into the off side
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot and runs it down towards third man for a single
bowled on a good length on the off, rocks forward and guides it to point
banged in short on middle and Wade swayed out of the way quickly, evaded that well, a snorter from Malinga

deveived by the slower one, Doherty had got out in similar fashion in the previous match, was into the shot too early was Wade and that landed short of mid-off, lucky to stay and get a run on top of that
short of a good length on middle, turns it wide of mid-on for a single
turned away off the back foot through the leg side for a single
short of a good length on the off, stands up nicely to that one and taps it to point
slides it on the pads once again and it's flicked past square leg for a couple more runs
bowled it short of a good length, picking off the runs easily here, run down to third man for a single
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot and drops it down into the off side
Another slower one from Malinga, lots of width on that one, sliced over cover for three runs, his bottom hand came off there, didn't pick the change in pace once again

short ball and Warner shaped up for the pull, connected well but not as well as he would have liked, got lots of elevation on that one, landed safely in the deep square leg region and three more to the Australians
Malinga bowls a big wide down the leg side, and it's called, lots of cloud cover now
slower one bowled on leg stump, probably pitched outside leg and cut in a hint, walked across to play that square, struck on the pads
another slower ball that he plays watchfully but not convincingly, pushed awkwardly towards mid-off
dropped that short on middle, a touch too short and Wade got out of the way, too high and it's called a wide

Malinga feeding Wade with a dose of slower ones, too many one would think having seen that shot, Wade deposited that miles behind deep midwicket, connected superbly, clean swing of the bat, that was murdered
Malinga paying for a poor line this time, pitched up well outside off and Wade drills that hard through mid-off and extra cover, an attacking start this
back of a length on middle, gets on the back foot to punch it into the off side
shortish on the off, jabbed it wide of midwicket for a couple more runs
ooh, a thick inside edge onto the pads, short of a good length and Warner tried to force that through the leg side
dropped that one slightly short on the off, stabbed it down towards mid-on, Kulasekara slipped on his follow through
pushed it fuller, on middle and off, driven soundly but straight to mid-off
shortish on middle and leg, turned away past Malinga at short fine leg, Malinga could have put in a better effort there, the dive slowing the ball down but only a hint, three more
pitched up on the off stump, driven forcefully but straight to mid-off
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot to mid-on
Warner goes for that, a big swing attempted over deep midwicket, it takes the outside edge and clears slip for a boundary, 50 up for Australia, streaky from Warner
connects well this time, Maharoof drops that short, Warner picks the length early and pulls it well over midwicket
more runs, uses the depth of the crease well, pitched up on the off and he moved back to just flick it past mid-on for a couple more
Kula bowls that full, steered through point and cover for two more runs
short of a good length, runs it down towards third man for a single
punched hard from Warner, short on the off and he cracks it past mid-off, moved back, picked the length early and dealt with it well
beaten, bowled on a good length this time and got it to move away, Warner fished for that, slightly inside the line and was beaten
bowled it short of a good length on middle, jabbed past midwicket into the deep for a couple more runs
shortish outside off, kept a little low, attempted the cut, got a thick underedge on the bounce to the keeper
bowls it short of a good length outside off, allows it through to the keeper
goodish length on leg stump, gets across and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, cracked hard but Dilshan does well at point to stop that

Warner didn't have an answer to that one, bowled on a good length and got it to cut away, Warner moved back and tried to play against the movement, tried to whip it through the leg side, got a thick outside edge towards third man
allows that one to go through does Wade
short ball on middle and jagged back in rap Wade on the gloves, a good over this from Maharoof after a disappointing first
slightly short on middle and off, pushed back down the pitch to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, punched off the back foot straight towards cover
on middle, shortish again, pushed off the back foot to mid-on
punched off the back foot into the leg side, another shortish delivery
gets on the back foot and turns it just wide of Malinga at short fine, just the single
short and wide, there to cut or so Wade thinks, a touch too close it seems in the end, misses
bowled it short of a length on middle, worked off the hips behind square for a single
bowled on a good length on the off, defended towards point off the front foot
goodish length outside off, gets forward and pushes it towards point, they steal a quick single and one more after Upul Tharanga fumbles
lovely shot from Wade, struck through the line, pitched it up and he drove it elegantly down the ground past mid-off
goodish length on leg stump, defended towards point from the crease
pushed it on a good length on middle, defended into the leg side
short of a good length on middle, makes room and chops it down towards point
angling in towards middle, holds its line, drops it in front of point to collect a single
bowled it towards middle and leg, angling down, tickled towards square leg
low full toss on the off, pushed gently towards extra cover
flighted on leg stump, driven straight towards midwicket
short ball outside off, rocks back and punches it towards deep cover for a single
bowled on a good length on middle, defended solidly in front of extra cover
bowled it short on leg stump, worked away wide of fine leg, Wade sprints back for the second
pitched it up full on the off, driven on the up towards mid-off
bowled it slightly short on middle and off, defended towards point
shortish on the off, punched standing tall on the back foot through point for a single
slightly short on leg stump, turns it behind square leg for an easy single
pushed it off the front foot through extra cover into the deep for a single
tossed up on the off, driven straight to extra cover this time
drops it just wide of point for a quick single, thought of a second but there was none
shortish on middle from round the wicket, punched in the direction of midwicket
short of a good length on the off, taps it towards point for a single
bowled it full on middle, driven through towards long-off for a single
short, gives some width, it's slashed hard towards third man for a single
around a good length on the off, rocks on the back foot and knocks it towards point
ooh, a good length ball that bounced more than Warner would have liked, got it a little high on the bat as he went through with the shot but it landed short of extra cover
shortish delivery on leg stump and it strikes him high on the pads
short of a good length, punched towards deep cover for an easy single
slightly short of a good length, knocks it down towards point
shortish outside off, chops it down towards point where it's fielded well
a touch short again, cracked straight to point once more
keeps it flat, bowled on a good length, driven straight back to the bowler
straying on the pads, clips the pads as he tries to work it square
flighted on the off, pushed down towards long-off for a single
driven through the line towards long-off for a single again, a tidy over from Dilshan
short of a good length on the off, rocks on the back foot and taps that towards cover
shortish on middle and off, defended down towards point
bowled it short on middle, pulled towards deep square leg for a single
short of a good length, Warner gets back and just jab-chips it over midwicket for a couple of runs
pushed it quicker and a touch fuller, Warner still opts to go back and work it past midwicket for a single
bowled it on a good length on middle, knocked down in the direction of square leg for a quick single
a bit of flight on that one and it lands short outside off, Wade waits for it to turn away and slashes it behind point for three runs, Tharanga gave chase and dragged it in
slightly short on the off, pushed off the back foot past extra cover for a single
tossed up on middle, defended cautiously towards extra cover

appeal for run-out, pushed off the front foot wide of extra cover, there is an attempt at a direct hit as Wade tries to steal a single to reach his half-century, Tharanga was the man, the ricohet off the stumps fetches them two more and takes Wade to 52, a solid knock from Wade, excellent start this for Australia
short of a good length, pushed off the back foot to extra cover
cracked off the front foot towards point
width and bowled full, allows Wade to free his arms, he cracks that through extra cover into the deep for a couple of runs
beaten, lovely delivery that was bowled on a good length and shot away to beat the outside edge
shortish outside off, it's cut away towards third man, he has to run across a few yards and Wade picks up a couple
short and wide, tries to crash it through the covers, has to reach for it, misses
bowled on a good length in the channel outside off, Wade shoulders arms to that one
bowled it short outside off, chopped it down towards point
bowled it slightly short outside off, cracked it through to deep cover for a single
bowled it on a good length outside off, defended towards point
steps out of his crease, that was held back by Dilshan, defended into the off side
floating it towards middle, defended to extra cover
turned away behind square leg for a single, thinking of a second but it's not there
punched it down towards long-on off the back foot
beaten, pushed it full outside off, Warner drove at that one inside the line, beaten
clipped away off the pads towards fine leg for a single
short of a good length, drops it down in front of slip
pitched up outside off, bowled at 147kmph, good pace that, tried to crack that through point but couldn't get his bat to it
around a good length on the pads, turned away gently through midwicket and there's enough time for them to sprint back for the second
bowled it on a good length on middle, defended off the back foot to mid-on
pitched up on the off and he has drilled that past mid-off, Maharoof dives but in vain and the boundary fetches Warner his half-century
lovely ball, pitched it up but got it to move away, Warner was eyeing that mid-off boundary again but was beaten by the movement
shortish on leg stump, whipped towards deep square leg for a single
short of a good length on the off, moves back and pushes it to point
bowled it full on the off, driven straight towards mid-off, firm but straight
slightly short on the off, knocks it down in front of point
creamed, absolutely thrashed, but straight to the fielder, pitched up and he cracked it straight to mid-off where Kulasekara did the hard work of getting behind it
no chance for him this time, was pitched on a length and he smote that through the line past the bowler, mid-off wasn't in range at all
another one, Prasad bowling too full again, in the slot for Warner who powered that through mid-off once more, three deliveries of almost identical length and line
angling in towards middle, defends it cautiously back towards the bowler

middled superbly, Dammika errs in length this time by bowling it short and Warner likes playing that shot, gets forward and pulls him powerfully over the long-on boundary, and it's caught by a spectator in the crowd
short of a good length and it's chopped towards cover
poor line given there is a short fine leg in place, low full toss on the pads and Wade flicks it away through square leg
short of a good length on the off, chopped it down behind point for a single
walked forward did Warner and Kula held it back, tried to jab it through square leg but it struck him on the thigh
bowled it on a good length on middle, Warner moved back and defended it to extra cover
pushed it full on leg stump, Warner plays it down to long-on and wants the second but Wade sends him back a little belatedly, Warner dives to make it back

An outstanding catch by Herath, for a moment it seemed Wade had struck it cleanly to send it over the ropes but it wasn't timed as well as initially thought, Herath was at long-on and Wade had enough on it to get it past him as he was standing a few yards inside the ropes, Herath though kept his eyes on the ball throughout, back-pedalled a few steps, stuck out one hand and snapped it while falling back, he made sure he caught it clean with his feet well inside the ropes, a stunning effort to bring an end to a superb opening stand
short of a length outside off, cut down straight to point
thick outside edge, short of a good length outside off and Watson pushes at that one inside the line, rolls down the third man boundary past slip
guided off the back foot with an open face
Six, Malinga bowls it short on middle with a fine leg up, Warner stays his ground and pulls it well behind square and it has enough on it to clear the ropes, just about
slower one bowled on a good length outside off, pushed through to extra cover
slower one bowled short outside leg stump, works it to short fine where Herath fumbles, allowing Warner a quick single
bowled it on a good length on the off, pushed it towards extra cover
angling in towards middle, defended on the off side with bat close to pad
Warner reaches his highest ODI score with a jab through midwicket
gets front and across to work it towards midwicket
shortish on the off, punched towards long-on off the back foot
flighted on leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
starts from round the wicket, goodish length on leg stump, holds its line, defended back to the bowler
pitched up on middle, driven straight towards extra cover
short of a good length, does well, giving himself some room and delicately guiding it past point for a couple of runs
slightly short on leg stump, punched towards extra cover, Warner refuses the single
floating it on leg stump, played gently towards midwicket
fired it quick outside leg stump, Warner went for the sweep, missed, was rapped on the pads
bowled it on a good length, plays it back to the bowler
short, Watson pulls that past midwicket for a single in the deep
short outside off, smacked off the back foot past extra cover for a couple in the deep
flighted on middle, driven towards long-off for a single
slightly short on the off, turns in just a hint, defended into the off side
shortish on the off, punched to long-on for a single
tossed up on middle, driven down towards long-on for a single
short on middle and off, pushed off the baqck foot to cover
quicker through the air, slightly short outside off, played it towards point
bowls it short on middle, punched straight to extra cover
flighted on the off, pushed down the ground to long-off for a single
fires it straight on leg stump, flicked away really fine, two more as Maharoof runs across from deep backward square leg to cut it off
shortish on middle, worked away off the back foot through square leg
pushed down the ground to long-on for a single
flighted on middle, pushed straight to extra cover where a misfield earns them a single
went on straight, bowled it flat, Watson made room to cut but missed
steps out and plays it down towards long-on for a single
pushed it full on the off, Warner pats it back down the pitch
flighted on leg stump, Watson steps out of the crease and flicks it square for a couple of runs
bowled it full from round the wicket on middle, defended into the leg side
full toss on middle, drilled down the ground towards long-on, Malinga dives to his left to cut that off
worked away behind square into the deep for a single
short on the off, slapped it back down the pitch towards the bowler
in the slot on leg stump, struck hard, uppishly, towards long-on, just the single
flighted on middle, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
bowled it short on the off, worked away off the back foot to square leg
whipped straight to square leg once again
forced it down the ground towards long-on for a single
angling on leg stump, worked gently behind square, enough time to come back for the second
clipped into the leg side for another single
slower one bowled on a good length, steered it wide of point for a couple of runs
punched that one through the line towards mid-off
slightly short on leg stump, turned it wide of midwicket for a single
short on middle, rolls his wrists over that one to play it to deep square leg
slower one bowled short outside off, mistimes a punch to extra cover
stroked that off the front foot on the up wide of mid-off for a single
pitched up on middle, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
bowled on a good length, struck back to Kulasekara who palms it off towards mid-off, a hint of bleeding there, struck him on the webbing
sliding it on a good length just outside leg stump, struck on the pads as he tries to clip it square
short of a good length on the off, punches it back towards the bowler
run-out attempt, missed the stumps did Jaywardene who took aim from midwicket, Warner tried for the single but would probably have been short had that hit
an excellent over, this, short of a good length and Watson just taps it to point
mistimes a drive wide of extra cover, Jayawardene dives full length and keeps them to just a single, raises the 50 stand

Watson goes, it's been a quiet Powerplay so far, that landed on leg stump, was a slower ball, tried to flick it square but ended up playing uppishly and it appeared to come off the top edge as well, Thirimanne ran in from deep square leg and took a safe catch
short of a good length on the off, punched towards cover from the crease

edged and four, short and wide, there to cut, gets a thick under-edge that beats Sangakkara and rolls down the third-man boundary to bring up his first ODI hundred, punches the gloves and celebrates with a leap while reaching the other end, a big landmark for Warner
short and slow, slapped but straight to extra cover
eases that off the front foot through the line to long-off
Kula gives Warner some width and he doesn't waste it, slashes it hard through point for a boundary
yorker length on middle, a good comeback, Warner can only dig it out in front of cover
bowled on a good length, Warner made room to that one and punched it towards cover
full on leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on, Malinga runs in and throws at the striker's end, a run-out attempt, Christian would have been out had Malinga hit direct
low full toss on the off, dug out towards Dilshan at point

bisects the gap this time between mid-off and extra cover, that was pitched up, Kula was aiming or another one in the blockhole but it didn't quite work out this time, drilled by Warner for a boundary
Christian's been fortunate this innings, that one nipped back in and Christian was beaten through the gate, it took the inside edge and rolled down the fine-leg boundary
slower one angling in on leg stump, tickled past square leg for a single
bowls a low full toss outside off, Warner made some room to steer that, ended up slicing it over point for a couple of runs
slower one bowled short outside off, punched past cover for a single
struck hard and over the bowler's head, pitched up and Christian drove that powerfully through the line, beat long-on who ran across but couldn't cut it off
slower one bowled short on middle, tapped into the leg side towards midwicket
floating it on leg stump, driven past midwicket into the deep for a couple of runs
slightly short on middle, chops it wide of point for one more
flighted on middle and off, driven past midwicket, who fumbles, for a single
on middle, fullish, pushed through the off side for a single
on a good length just outside off, defended in front of point
some turn there, landed short on leg and spun towards middle, drops it down in the leg side
yorker first up, excellent delivery, in the blockhole on leg stump and Warner can only push it back to the bowler
superbly hit, slower one and Warner picked it, was a long hop and Warner smashed it over midwicket for a one-bounce four
bowled it full on middle, that was driven down to long-off for a single

Christian goes! Reiffel upholds the appeal, bowled on a good length and it nipped back in, Christian walked into the shot, got a faint inside edge and Sangakkara dived to his left to take a good low catch
bowled it full outside off, reaches for it and drives it straight to extra cover
full outside off, cracked firmly towards deep cover for a single to retain the strike
David Hussey's gone! Tossed up and Hussey was drawn into playing the drive, a soft dismissal in the end, pushes it straight back to the bowler who takes it sharply, timing his jump well
Herath bowls a short ball on leg stump, Clarke pulls that really fine, two for Clarke
comes down the track and drives it down to long-on for a single
slower, short on the off, cut down towards deep point for a couple of runs
bowled short on the off, punched back towards the bowler
worked away off the back foot in the deep for a single
pitched up outside off, played towards long-off for a single
Clarke gets across to a straight delivery from Prasad, works it past midwicket for a single
pushed it full on middle, driven towards long-off for a single
short of a good length on the off, defended towards the bowler
full and quick outside off, Clarke went after that one, looking to drive it through extra cover, missed
that is smashed, gets it in the middle this time, similar delivery to the previous one and Clarke plays it much straighter, caressing it to beat Malinga's drive at mid-off
short on middle, punched it towards long-on for a single
tossed up, pushed off the front foot towards midwicket
Clarke seizes the length early, waiting for it to turn away and cutting it uppishly but safely behind point for a boundary
dances down the track this time and flicks it through square leg for a single
pushed past extra cover into the deep for a single
flighted on middle, driven straight towards midwicket
slower one bowled full on middle, cutting away, gets a thick outside edge as he tries to play it through the line, a single to third man
slower one bowled short outside off, dabbed it in front of point
deliberately done, Malinga continues to go for runs, bowled it full and Clarke delicately opened the face to guide it wide of third man
slower one bowled full outside off, steers that into the ground and over point for a couple of runs
slower one bowled on middle, gets across to play it square for a couple more runs
played straight to Dilshan at point, full outside off and he square-drives it but straight to the fielder
quicker ball bowled outside leg stump, tried to work it square, was struck on the pads
firmly hit but deep midwicket cuts it off, driven all along the ground
angling in towards leg, turns it around for a single
flighted on leg stump, drives it down the ground to long-on for a single
fires it down the leg side and it's called a wide
comes down the track and tickles it fine for a single
short ball outside off, cracked off the back foot towards deep cover to keep strike
Malinga's bleeding runs today, pitched up, in the slot for Warner and it's hammered back past the bowler
another one bowled full, made room and sliced that over extra cover for a couple of runs
yorker length this time, almost but not quite, dug out wide of cover for a single
Clarke connects, and does so really well, it was bowled full on middle, Clarke made room and creamed that but straight to mid-off
slower one bowled short, pulled through square leg for a single
slightly short outside off, dabs it off the back foot towards point
low full toss on leg stump, a poor ball given fine leg is up, clipped away past that fielder for four more
pitched up outside off this time, Clarke steps out to drive that wide of long-off for two more
low full toss outside off this time, driven to long-on for a single to raise the 50-stand
superbly done by Warner, smart cricket, third man is up, that was a slower one, he made room and just placed it between point and short third
short outside off and this time he cuts it wide of point and Clarke runs superbly, calling for the third and making it in time
bowled it full outside off, driven wide of long-off for two more, 16 off the over, Australia are charging
slower one from Malinga, Warner tries to smack him through the line, gets a thick outside edge and it falls short of third man
Clarke's turn to get the outside edge this time, the slower one again and Clarke, too, had planned to go downtown, got a thick edge and to the third-man boundary

Malinga gets a wicket, finally, a slower one again and Clarke, looking to go over midwicket this time, mistimed the attempted pull and Jayawardene took a well-judged catch running to his right from midwicket
slower one, gets to his 150 with a dab wide of point for a single, he likes scoring big
slower one bowled short on leg stump, struck him on the glove as he tried to work it around
slower one again, the offcutter, guided behind point for two runs by Hussey
hit hard, was a low full toss on the off, smacked wide of long-off for a couple of runs, they've runs these twos brilliantly today
walks across and taps that fullish delivery through midwicket for a single
Hussey flicks that good-length ball past midwicket for a single
that's gone through Kulasekara, bowled it full and Warner drilled it past the bowler, wide of long-on, for two more
pitched up and he swings that towards deep square leg for a single
good length on middle, comes down the track and gets it past midwicket, Warner calls for the second and makes it back in time, excellent stamina, brings up the 300 for Australia
slower one bowled short, slapped uppishly towards long-off for a single
bowled it full outside off, Hussey made room to launch that over extra cover but couldn't connect
superbly timed, got under it this time, was a length ball and right in the slot, he made room and lofted it cleanly over the long-off boundary
the slower one and Hussey is into the pull too early, misses out as he tries to slog it over midwicket
length ball again, driven hard but to long-off where Dilshan fields
Warner gets an inside edge on the thigh as he tries to swing that back to Melbourne, just a single in the end
full toss and it's clubbbed towards the bowler, Dhammika holds his hand out and is smacked, got struck on the palm, all's well now, just a couple in the end
a mistimed pull to midwicket, a quick single taken
Hussey has several such hits to his name, a length ball from Dhammika and it's swung miles over the deep midwicket fence
slapped to Jayawardene at extra cover at the edge of the circle, pinches a quick single
smashed down the ground to long-on and Hussey makes it back well in time, he's quick
bowled'im! Was the offcutter, landed on leg and cut away as he tried to pull that over midwicket, missed and the stumps were pegged back

inn2.comm: Brett Lee starts with one down the leg side
full swinging and wide, Jayawardene is tempted by that one, looks to drive through the off but is beaten
on legstump, Mahela looks to clip it to the leg side, rolls off the thigh pad towards backward square leg
pitched up and on off stump, a crisp drive towards extra cover by Dilshan, a diving stop there by Doherty
swinging and full outside off once more from Lee, this time Mahela connects well, crunches it towards cover, Michael Hussey gets in the way to cut off any chance of a run
back of a length and outside off, Mahela waits on the back foot and calmly steers it towards third man for a single
another wide one down the leg side
length ball heading for off, defended to the leg side for a single to end the over
overpitched by Hilfenhaus, whipped nonchalantly for a four to the midwicket boundary, Dilshan doesn't need a sighter
wonderful comeback from Hilfenhaus, short of a length and seams away a touch, Dilshan goes for an on-the-up drive but is beaten
a tight single there, on the pads, Dilshan defends it towards square leg for a run, Mahela responds to the call early

Mahela charges down the ground and looks to launch the ball over extra cover, gets a thick outside edge and the ball soars towards third man, luckily for Sri Lanka it doesn't carry to the fielder there
slides this down the leg side for another free run
a well-timed drive from Dilshan, not so well placed, towards cover

an adventurous shot from Dilshan, shuffles across and whips the ball over midwicket, not as a clean a hit as the one he began the over with, but still has the legs to beat the chasing fielder to the rope
Lee bowls on a good length, Jayawardene just drops it in front of extra cover and steals a quick single
that's gone past fine leg, banged in short on leg stump and he pulls it fine, lands just short of the ropes, a one bounce four
turns it past mid-on for a quick single
beaten as that one nips back in, lands on a good length and shoots in to beat Mahela through the gate
drops that short on the off stump, knocks it down into the off side, thinks of a single but Dilshan sends him back
bowled on a good length on the off, defended solidly into the leg side off the back foot
that flew off the bat, slashed really hard by Dilshan, took the outside edge and beat Lee at third man to he boundary
appeal for a catch, Dilshan dances down the track and tries to whip it through the leg side, tried to flick it, it clipped the pad on the way to the keeper, the back pad
short of a good length on the off, stands tall and taps it towards point
angling towards the pads, tries to flick it fine, brushes the pads and they get a leg bye
beautifully picked, landed slightly short on middle and leg and Jayawardene shuffled across a hint to pick it over square leg
came down the pitch, aiming to take it off a length and drive it through the covers but it moved away after pitching, missed
fires it full on middle, flicked away towards fine leg for a single
Jayawardene does it nicely, was a slower  ball and he just moved away to chip it over the covers for a couple of runs
outstanding from Jayawardene, Lee drags it short and Jayawardene gets into position early to pull it over square leg
Mahela has to go, couldn't resist fishing for a good length ball outside off that moved away, was trying to glide it to third man, got a thin edge and Wade took an easy catch
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot to point
bowls that on a good length on the off, pushed through to mid-off
dropped it short on leg stump and he pulls it fine but can't get it past the short-fine fielder
angling in towards leg stump and going beyond, tried to flick that over midwicket, was struck on the pads
short of a good length, gets on the back foot and guides it towards point
that's a trademark Sangakkra drive, pitched up and he just eased it through extra cover for three runs
back of a length on middle, mistimes an attempted pull, a single towards midwicket
lovely timing, just a flick, bowled full on middle and leg and he squeezes it past midwicket for three more runs
bowled on a good length on the off, gets forward, dabs it into the leg side and takes a single
short of a length outside off, punched off the back foot towards point
the slower ball, bowled short, Dilshan had committed himself to playing the pull, didn't pick the change of pace but was fortunate, got a top-edge over the keeper's head for a boundary
bowled it short outside off, slapped it straight to point
a good length ball that cut away, Dilshan played it from the crease, defending it towards point

bowled'im! Slightly wide of the crease and got it to angle in, nipped back in further as Dilshan tried to drive it through the line, it beat him through the fate and pegged back middle stump, Lee's seen off the openers
A flowing drive from Sangakkara, that goes straight to mid-off
around a good length on the off, worked past square leg, Lee gathers and returns a powerful throw but Sanga has made it back
angling it away from the left-hander, Sangakkara opts to leave it be
gifts him with some width and Sanga cashes in, flaying it through point and cover, a square-drive, for a boundary
poor ball, a short ball down the leg side and Sanga helps it on its way to the fine-leg boundary
four more, streaky this time, pitched up outside off, tried to drive it square but ended up getting a thick inside edge past the keeper for four more, three in a row
in the channel outside off, a hint of away movement, Chandimal lets it go
ooh, a touch too early in closing the face there, almost offered a catch to the bowler, landed just short of Watson in his follow through
a thick outside off, bowling on a good length, moved away after pitching, a single to third man
getting some swing, gets forward and plays it towards extra cover

appeal for lbw, that swung back in, the interesting thing to see is whether that struck him just outside the line, may have just done that, Reiffel thinks so, landed around off stump and struck Sanga on the back pad. In fact, it would have gone over
bowled it full on the off, defended off the front foot to extra cover
outside leg stump, tickled past that short square leg fielder, who misfields
bowls on a good length outside off, defended in front of cover
a touch fuller towards middle, holding its line, defended off the front foot
floating it on the off, drives it back towards the bowler
short, waiting for it to turn away, slaps it straight to point
shortish, turning away off a good length, swats it straight to cover
short of a good length just outside off, left alone to the keeper

appeal for caught-behind, Wade went up immediately, some swing for Watson helping him here, lands on a good length and moves in, Sangakkara didn't get a bat to it, clipped the thigh on the way to the keeper
bowled it full on the off, knocked down into the off side
in the channel outside off and that one holds its line, Sanga lets it go
some inward movement again, bowled full, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
bowled it full outside off, knocked way into the off side
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover
charges out of the crease and cracks it wide of mid-off, just the single

turning in from a good length on the off, gets a stride out and defends
flighted on middle, drives it down the ground towards long-on
ooh, was almost deceived by the flight, tossed up and he came forward but not quite to the pitch, went through with the shot and pushed it uppishly towards long-off
bowls it full on the off, a hint of outsiwng there for Watson, pushed it cautiously towards extra cover
lands on a length on off and middle, defended solidly towards mid-off
driven firmly, gets to the pitch this time and plays it through the line, fielded well at extra cover
short ball on middle and Chandimal likes playing that shot, first boundary in some time, more than four overs, rocks back and pulls it square
swinging away just a hint, follows the ball this time and taps it towards point
jagged back in and Chandimal got an inside edge as he went across to that one
worked away through square leg into the deep for a single
slightly short on the off, punches it down towards long-on
floating it down the leg side and it's called a wide
shortish on middle, worked away through square leg for a single
pushed through the line to long-off for a single
comes down the track, takes it on the full, and plays it to long-off
tossed up on the off, holds its line, knocked straight to extra cover
bowls on a good length, a hint of inswing this time, wide enough for Sanga to let it be
goodish length on the off, pushes it towards extra cover off the front foot
steps out of his crease, takes it from a length and smashes it back through Watson, who gets a hand to it, to keep them to two runs
in the corridor outside off and holds its line this time, left alone
banged in short, jabs that uppishly towards deep square leg for a single
fullish on the off, pushes it gently towards mid-on and steals a quick single
Chandimal tries to paddle that fine, is struck on the helmet as it takes the top-edge and crashes into the grill
gets forward and turns it towards square leg for a single
shortish on the off, punched towards deep cover for a single
bowled it flat on the off stump, defended towards extra cover
comes out of the crease and drives that down towards long-on for a single
flighted, Chandimal got out of the crease, got to the pitch and drove it to long-off
strikes immediately! Short outside off, Chandimal moves away to cut that uppishly, straight into the hands of Pattinson at point, good bounce for Hussey there
short of a good length on the off, continuing riund the wicket, played to cover
leans forward and plays it to cover again
lands full, leans forward and chips that over the in-field on the off side for a couple of runs
fires in a delivery in the blockhole from round the wicket, just about dug out by Thirimanne
shortish, cut towards point, no single on offer there
angling in towards middle, Sangakkara flicks it through square leg for a single
turns in from outside off, rocks back and turns it to midwicket
waits for it to turn in and punches that wide of point
gets across and bunts it towards square leg for a single
gets front and across and pushes that one back down the pitch
slightly quicker through the air, short outside off, Sanga tries to play the late-cut, misses
keeping it tight, just around off stump, bowled it flat, defended into the off side
pitched up, squeezed towards point, calls for a single but it's not available
drives that towards long-off for a single
floating it on the off, driven past Hussey for a single
fires that short outside leg stump, looked to sweep it fine but could not

gets front and across and taps that back down the pitch

turned towards square leg off the back foot
comes down the track and nudges it towards midwicket

straying on the pads, flicked towards short fine leg, just the single

short ball outside off, chops it down straight to point

gets on the front foot and steers that on the bounce towards point
short of a good length, Thirmanne gives himself room to smote it over the covers but misses
fends it into the leg side for a single, was slightly short
shortish on leg stump, turned away behind square for a couple of runs
Under pressure to step up the scoring, Sangakkra loses his wicket, was on a good length and he stood his ground and tried to clear mid-off, mistimed it completely and Watson at mid-off took a dolly
short of a good length outside off, shoulders arms to let that through
short of a good length again, gets back and defends it in front of the bowler
a touch fuller but onlu just, drops it back down the pitch to the bowler
pushes that off the front foot towards midwicket
darts back in from a good length, gets an inside edge on the pads and they steal a single
goodish length on the off, drives it back towards the bowler off the front foot
stroked firmly but straight towards extra cover

a maiden, Sri Lanka are fighting it tough to get going, pitched on a length and it's driven straight to mid-off

played into the off side

played straight to midwicket
guided off the front foot towards point

a slower ball gone bad, slipped out of his hand and called a no-ball, well above waist height
struck uppishly towards mid-on, sneaks in a quick single

four more, shortish on the off, makes room and jabs that hard past a diving mid-on for four more
nicely timed, a well-deserved half-century reached witha  delicate steer past point, a good fightback, a whirlwind knock, off just 33 balls
Kulaksekara is turning it on, a full toss on the off, moves away and thumps that over mid-off for a one bounce four
fullish, mistimes a drive down the ground, just a single this time

the slog-sweep and it goes all the way, Wade must be getting nervous, tossed up on the off and he's swung it cleanly over deep midwicket

chips that one over the bowler's ehad for a couple more runs

pitched it full outside off, squeezed through extra cover for a single

short ball on middle, helps it wide of short fine for a single

cut fiercely by Tharanga, quicker through the air, landed short and he bisected the gap between short third and point, raises his half-century, is not accustomed to batting in the middle order is Tharanga but he's done a fine job here
two more, that was a short ball bowled down the leg side, helped wide of fine leg for a couple more runs

Tharanga goes! Is that the decisive blow? Pitched on a length and he had to go for it, strikes it well but not enough in it to take it over the ropes, David Hussey at long-on holds his nerve and takes a comfortable catch
slower one, pushed away into the off side for a quick single
Prasad, you beauty! That's a Sehwagesque smack over the covers, good length ball, he made room and dispatched it with utter disdain over deep cover
yorker length on middle, defended in front of midwicket for a quick single
full toss, superbly timed, two more, Herath slipped while running and that prevented the third, just a punch over the covers
a wide down the leg side, Lee errs in line, one more to the score
ooh, short ball and he jabbed it uppishly, landed just wide of Clarke at midwicket, just the single

short ball, rocks back and pulls it in front of square for a single

more frenzy in the middle, a slower ball, Prasad wanted to work that to the leg side, he had shuffled across the stumps off the pad towards the keeper, Prasad wanted a single and hared off, the non-striker didn't, Wade attempts to throw down the stumps, Prasad has to  dive back
aims for the yorker, ends up a full toss outside off, slapped towards point, lands just short of the fielder

Watson has struck, Herath is dismissed as he goes for his favourite slog shot, a length delivery is struck well by Herath, but Doherty had cleverly been placed well short of the rope, it ends up as a simple catch, only one wicket in hand now, Malinga was off-colour with the ball can he redeem himself with the bat?
a slower ball outside off, poked to the off side
a length ball outside off, driven towards cover, they don't go for the single, Prasad will be on strike next over, 20 needed off 12
bowled it full on middle, flicked it square for just the single
swings at that one, just a fraction outside off but makes no contact, a dot ball for Australia
full and he tries to smash that down the ground, ends up getting a thick outside edge towards third man, lands to him on the bounce, Pattinson didn't go for it
Prasad swings that straight to deep square leg, fullish on middle and he struck it well but found the fielder

superb yotker from Lee, Malinga could not bring his bat down in time and could only sneak a bye, Prasad stole the bye running at the danger end and Lee collected Wade's throw and aimed inaccurately at the non-striker's end
another miss, pitched up outside off and Prasad had a wild swing at that one, wanted the bye but Malinga sent him back, rightly, a dot ball, the pressure grows on Sri Lanka
A slower legcutter that Malinga fails to connect, had a wild swing but couldn't get his bat to it

Another slower one, Malinga swings it high but not far enough and finds deep square leg where Michael Hussey judges it well, Australia win the first final. Struck that really high did Malinga, didn't get hold but he had no choice but to go for it. Clarke heaves a sigh of relief, his team was given a real scare
